to all those fine men and women we have lost throughout the bloody war in Iraq and Afghanistan...Let us show that we still honor our brothers that have fallen in combat, those that will continue to fall for the safety of our country and all those that have been severely injured and will never again be able to live a normal life without some type of prostetic limb or wheelchair...\n\nTo date we have lost 4425 soldiers in Iraq and 1329 soldiers in Afghanistan. Currenty 31902 soldierss have been wounded in Iraq and 7266 have been wounded in Afghanistan.  \n\n1. Supporting all troops\n\n2. Showing respect to the families of the men and women we have lost\',\n                                      \'Score\' => 1455068,\n                                      \'Categories\' => $VAR1->{\'Categories\'},\n                                      \'MiscInfo\' => \'<?xml version=\"1.0\" encoding=\"UTF-8\"?>\n<cause>\n  <description>Show tribute to all those fine men and women we have lost throughout the bloody war in Iraq and Afghanistan...Let us show that we still honor our brothers that have fallen in combat, those that will continue to fall for the safety of our country and all those that have been severely injured and will never again be able to live a normal life without some type of prostetic limb or wheelchair...\r\n\r\nTo date we have lost 4425 soldiers in Iraq and 1329 soldiers in Afghanistan. Currenty 31902 soldierss have been wounded in Iraq and 7266 have been wounded in Afghanistan.  \n\n1. Supporting all troops\n\n2. Showing respect to the families of the men and women we have lost</description>\n  <mission>Honor all those who have given their lives for our countries freedom and security</mission>\n  <name>Honor our Fallen Soldiers</name>\n  <canonical-url>http://www.causes.com/causes/2719</canonical-url>\n  <member-count type=\"integer\">1455068</member-count>\n  <total-raised type=\"decimal\">35.0</total-raised>\n  <photo-url>https://causes-prod.s3.amazonaws.com/photos/O3/Zu/Yl/FP/14/S8/v8/AqS.jpg</photo-url>\n</cause>\n\',\n                                      \'Title\' => \'Honor our Fallen Soldiers\'\n                                    }, \'Com::elle::bLeaf::EvidenceGenerator::News\' ),\n                 \'Results\' => [\n                                bless( {\n                                         \'System\' => \'OpenCalais\',\n                                         \'Relevance\' => \'0.857\',\n                                         \'Contents\' => \'Iraq\',\n                                         \'Type\' => \'country\',\n                                         \'Count\' => \'3\',\n                                         \'Normalized\' => \'Iraq\'\n                                       }, \'Com::elle::bLeaf::EvidenceGenerator::Entity\' ),\n                                bless( {\n                                         \'System\' => \'OpenCalais\',\n                                         \'Relevance\' => \'0.857\',\n                                         \'Contents\' => \'Afghanistan\',\n                                         \'Type\' => \'country\',\n                                         \'Count\' => \'3\',\n                                         \'Normalized\' => \'Afghanistan\'\n                                       }, \'Com::elle::bLeaf::EvidenceGenerator::Entity\' ),\n                                bless( {\n                                         \'Contents\' => \'Iraq\',\n                                         \'System\' => \'Named Entity Recognition\',\n                                         \'Type\' => \'location\',\n                                         \'Normalized\' => \'Iraq\'\n                                       }, \'Com::elle::bLeaf::EvidenceGenerator::Entity\' ),\n                                bless( {\n                                         \'Contents\' => \'Afghanistan\',\n                                         \'System\' => \'Named Entity Recognition\',\n                                         \'Type\' => \'location\',\n                                         \'Normalized\' => \'Afghanistan\'\n                                       }, \'Com::elle::bLeaf::EvidenceGenerator::Entity\' )\n                              ],\n                 \'Reviews\' => [],\n                 \'Polarities\' => {\n                                   \'Iraq\' => \'\',\n                                   \'Afghanistan\' => \'\'\n                                 },\n                 \'EvidenceGenerator\' => undef\n               }, \'Com::elle::bLeaf::EvidenceGenerator::Evidence\' );\n'),('$VAR1 = [\n          bless( {\n                   \'URL\' => \'http://api.causes.com/causes/1413.xml\',\n                   \'SourceText\' => \'Causes.com: Cause 1413\'\n                 }, \'Com::elle::bLeaf::EvidenceGenerator::NewsSource\' ),\n          \'End Child Prostitution, Child Pornography and Trafficking of Children for Sexual Purposes\'\n        ];\n','$VAR1 = bless( {\n                 \'SelectedResults\' => [\n                                        \'Facebook\',\n                                        \'United States\'\n                                      ],\n                 \'Categories\' => {},\n                 \'MyNews\' => bless( {\n                                      \'Sources\' => [\n                                                     bless( {\n                                                              \'URL\' => \'http://api.causes.com/causes/1413.xml\',\n                                                              \'SourceText\' => \'Causes.com: Cause 1413\'\n                                                            }, \'Com::elle::bLeaf::EvidenceGenerator::NewsSource\' )\n                                                   ],\n                                      \'Links\' => [],\n                                      \'Contents\' => \'The causes of Commercial Sexual Exploitation of Children (CSEC) are complex and patterns differ among countries and regions. For example, in some areas the commercial sexual exploitation of children is clearly related to foreign child sex tourism, in others it is associated with the local demand. In most countries, girls represent 80 to 90% of the victims, although in some places boys predominate.\n\nAs is the case for other worst forms of child labour, severe poverty, the possibility of relatively high earnings, low value attached to education, family dysfunction, a cultural obligation to help support the family or the need to earn money to simply survive are all factors that make children vulnerable to CSEC.\n\nThere are other non-economic factors that also push children into commercial sexual exploitation. Children who are at greatest risk of becoming victims of CSEC are those that have previously experienced physical or sexual abuse. A family environment of little protection, where caregivers are absent or where there is a high level of violence or alcohol or drug consumption, induces boys and girls to run away from home, making them highly susceptible to abuse.\n\nNOTE ON DONATING: Donations made by US citizens or residents to this Facebook Cause are tax deductible.  Non-deductible donations may also be made to ECPAT International at: https://www.paypal.com/th/cgi-bin/webscr?cmd=_flow&SESSION=MmS1D7HVi966WrAZYiv6e2_QQawyV-HgpcxDlF7GLRRUQDCSE7QsG-Uc9LS&dispatch=5885d80a13c0db1f9fecf49521b3f5af727cc8f9db6c1fecf4abf56207eb6b8e\n\n\n1. Children should not have any part in the sex trade\n\n2. People who exploit vulnerable children should be found and locked away\n\n3. Resources should be available for exploited children for mental and physical help\',\n                                      \'Score\' => 1390293,\n                                      \'Categories\' => $VAR1->{\'Categories\'},\n                                      \'MiscInfo\' => \'<?xml version=\"1.0\" encoding=\"UTF-8\"?>\n<cause>\n  <description>The causes of Commercial Sexual Exploitation of Children (CSEC) are complex and patterns differ among countries and regions. For example, in some areas the commercial sexual exploitation of children is clearly related to foreign child sex tourism, in others it is associated with the local demand. In most countries, girls represent 80 to 90% of the victims, although in some places boys predominate.\r\n\r\nAs is the case for other worst forms of child labour, severe poverty, the possibility of relatively high earnings, low value attached to education, family dysfunction, a cultural obligation to help support the family or the need to earn money to simply survive are all factors that make children vulnerable to CSEC.\r\n\r\nThere are other non-economic factors that also push children into commercial sexual exploitation. Children who are at greatest risk of becoming victims of CSEC are those that have previously experienced physical or sexual abuse. A family environment of little protection, where caregivers are absent or where there is a high level of violence or alcohol or drug consumption, induces boys and girls to run away from home, making them highly susceptible to abuse.\r\n\r\nNOTE ON DONATING: Donations made by US citizens or residents to this Facebook Cause are tax deductible.  Non-deductible donations may also be made to ECPAT International at: https://www.paypal.com/th/cgi-bin/webscr?cmd=_flow&amp;SESSION=MmS1D7HVi966WrAZYiv6e2_QQawyV-HgpcxDlF7GLRRUQDCSE7QsG-Uc9LS&amp;dispatch=5885d80a13c0db1f9fecf49521b3f5af727cc8f9db6c1fecf4abf56207eb6b8e\r\n\n\n1. Children should not have any part in the sex trade\n\n2. People who exploit vulnerable children should be found and locked away\n\n3. Resources should be available for exploited children for mental and physical help</description>\n  <mission>Protect children from the sex trade</mission>\n  <name>End Child Prostitution, Child Pornography and Trafficking of Children for Sexual Purposes</name>\n  <canonical-url>http://www.causes.com/causes/1413</canonical-url>\n  <member-count type=\"integer\">1390293</member-count>\n  <total-raised type=\"decimal\">40607.39</total-raised>\n  <photo-url>https://causes-prod.s3.amazonaws.com/photos/si/Zk/Ul/H8/ft/XT/gl/GXS.jpg</photo-url>\n</cause>\n\',\n                                      \'Title\' => \'End Child Prostitution, Child Pornography and Trafficking of Children for Sexual Purposes\'\n                                    }, \'Com::elle::bLeaf::EvidenceGenerator::News\' ),\n                 \'Results\' => [\n                                bless( {\n                                         \'System\' => \'OpenCalais\',\n                                         \'Relevance\' => \'0.524\',\n                                         \'Contents\' => \'Facebook\',\n                                         \'Type\' => \'company\',\n                                         \'Count\' => \'1\',\n                                         \'Normalized\' => \'Facebook Inc\'\n                                       }, \'Com::elle::bLeaf::EvidenceGenerator::Entity\' ),\n                                bless( {\n                                         \'System\' => \'OpenCalais\',\n                                         \'Relevance\' => \'0.524\',\n                                         \'Contents\' => \'United States\',\n                                         \'Type\' => \'country\',\n                                         \'Count\' => \'1\',\n                                         \'Normalized\' => \'United States\'\n                                       }, \'Com::elle::bLeaf::EvidenceGenerator::Entity\' ),\n                                bless( {\n                                         \'Contents\' => \'CSEC\',\n                                         \'System\' => \'Named Entity Recognition\',\n                                         \'Type\' => \'organization\',\n                                         \'Normalized\' => \'CSEC\'\n                                  