enting suicide through research, education and advocacy, and to reaching out to people with mental disorders and those impacted by suicide.\',\n                                      \'Score\' => 596135,\n                                      \'Categories\' => $VAR1->{\'Categories\'},\n                                      \'MiscInfo\' => \'<?xml version=\"1.0\" encoding=\"UTF-8\"?>\n<cause>\n  <description>Suicide: A word that no one likes to hear.  Having a friend or family member take their life, leaves an empty hole of unanswered questions.\r\nDepression is still heavily stigmatized in society, programs need to be visible to help those obtain the help they need.\r\n\r\n* More people die by suicide each day than every person that died in the Sept 9-11 attacks.\r\n* Suicide is the second (Canada) and third (USA) leading cause of death for youth between the ages of 10 and 24.\r\n* By the age of 18, 1 in 20 youth will have made a suicide attempt. \r\n* Someone dies by suicide every 40 seconds\r\n* For every teen that dies by suicide, 400 report attempting suicide.\r\n\r\nWe have setup this cause to have some subsections in order to help people find the resources they require.\r\n\r\nFor support in depression, visit: http://www.facebook.com/group.php?gid=5151821693\r\nFor discussions around the topic of suicide, visit: http://www.facebook.com/group.php?gid=13774625071\r\n\r\nDue to the sensitive nature of the subject matter, we ask that you use the above groups if applicable.\r\n\r\nIf you are currently in crisis,\r\ncall 1-800-SUICIDE or 1-800-273-TALK (8255). \r\nSamaritans UK 08457 90 90 90 (UK) 1850 60 90 90 (ROI) http://www.samaritans.org\r\nMalaysia contact 03 - 7958144/45\r\nAustralia call LifeLine 13 11 14 or in Victoria - Suicide Help Line 1300 651 251.\r\n\r\nOther Resources:\r\n* Suicide Survivors Group: http://www.facebook.com/group.php?gid=2380414449\r\n* Take the pledge to break the silence: http://www.breaksilence.com\r\n* Help educate others through yo